{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2016}} {{Infobox person | name = Alexander Viktorovich Kutikov | image = File:Александр Кутиков.jpg | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1952|04|13}} | birth_place = [[Moscow]] | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) --> | death_place = | nationality = [[Russia]]n | other_names = | occupation = Musician and businessman | years_active = | known_for = [[Mashina Vremeni]] | notable_works = }} '''Alexander Viktorovich Kutikov''' ({{lang-ru|Александр Викторович Кутиков}}; 13 April 1952 in [[Moscow]]<ref>[http://www.jig.ru/index4.php/2009/12/20/beseda-s-aleksandrom-kutikovym.html Беседа с Александром Кутиковым. Международная Еврейская Газета — МЕГ<!-- Заголовок добавлен ботом -->]</ref>) is a [[Soviet Union|Soviet]]/[[Russia]]n [[rock musician]], [[record producer|producer]], and businessman. He was an avid fan of groups such as the Beatles during his secondary school years. He later became the [[Bass guitar|bass-guitarist]] and one of the [[singer]]s of the Soviet [[rock band]] [[Mashina Vremeni]], from 1971 to 1976.<ref>{{cite web|url={{Allmusic|class=artist|id=p653080/biography|pure_url=yes}}|title=Biography: Mashina Vremeni|last=Jaszi|first=Sabrina |publisher=[[Allmusic]]|accessdate=13 April 2010}}</ref> The band was temporarily interrupted because of internal quarrels and compulsory military service of all bandmates, but was reunited in 1979 and stayed intact ever since. They became famous in the USSR and in Eastern Europe for composing the soundtrack of ''[[Dusha]]'' (Soul), released in 1981. He is also a president of the [[sound recording]] [[company]] Sintez Records.<ref name=autogenerated2>[http://teleweek.ru/49818 ТЕЛЕНЕДЕЛЯ — Взгляд назад — Александр Кутиков: жену я себе украл]</ref>
Kutikov wrote the music and performed the vocals for the famous song "[[Povorot]]" by [[Mashina Vremeni]].
