[[File:Andre Kudelski - World Economic Forum Annual Meeting Davos 2010.jpg|thumb|André Kudelski at the [[World Economic Forum]] Annual Meeting 2010]]
'''André Kudelski''' (born 26 May 1960 in [[Lausanne]]), is a [[Switzerland|Swiss]] engineer of a [[Poles|Polish]] descent, who is the [[Chair (official)|Chairman of the Board]] and [[Chief Executive Officer]] of the [[Kudelski Group]].
André Kudelski obtained a degree in physical engineering from the [[École Polytechnique Fédérale de Lausanne]] (Switzerland) in 1984. He then held the position of R&D Engineer at Kudelski SA and in [[Silicon Valley]], before becoming Pay TV Product Manager and then Director of [[Nagravision]], Kudelski SA's pay TV division. In 1991, André Kudelski succeeded his father [[Stefan Kudelski]] to the post of President and Chief Executive Officer of Kudelski SA. He has been a member of Kudelski SA's Board of Directors since 1987. He is also Chairman of the Board's Strategy Committee.
André Kudelski sits on the Board of the [[Edipresse Group]], of [[Nestlé]], of [[Swiss International Air Lines]] and of [[Dassault Systemes]] (France), among others. In addition, he is a member of the Advisory Board of [[Credit Suisse]] Group and of the management committee of [[economiesuisse]]. He is a member of the Steering Committee of the [[Bilderberg Group]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bilderbergmeetings.org/governance.html |title=Steering Committee |work=bilderbergmeetings.org |publisher=[[Bilderberg Group]] |accessdate=2014-02-08 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140311013611/http://www.bilderbergmeetings.org/governance.html |archivedate=March 11, 2014 }}</ref>
In 1995, the [[World Economic Forum]] nominated André Kudelski as a "Global Leader for Tomorrow". He received an [[Emmy award]] in [[New York City]] from the [[National Academy of Television Arts and Sciences|National Academy of Arts and Sciences]] for his company's achievements in the area of [[Pay-TV]] [[conditional access]] and [[Content scrambling system|scrambling systems]] in 1996.<ref>{{Cite web | title = André KUDELSKI | accessdate = 2007-08-21 | url = http://www.nestle.com/AllAbout/Governance/NestleManagement/AllCvs/BoardDirectors/AndreKUDELSKI.htm
| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20070927015159/http://www.nestle.com/AllAbout/Governance/NestleManagement/AllCvs/BoardDirectors/AndreKUDELSKI.htm| archivedate= 27 September 2007 <!--DASHBot-->| deadurl= no}}</ref>
In 2002, André Kudelski was on the ''[[Forbes]]'' List of the World's Richest People, being a billionaire at the time.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Forbes.com: Forbes World's Richest People 2002 |accessdate=2007-08-21 |url=https://www.forbes.com/finance/lists/10/2002/LIR.jhtml?passListId=10&passYear=2002&passListType=Person&uniqueId=4G6N&datatype=Person |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080519030333/http://www.forbes.com/finance/lists/10/2002/LIR.jhtml?passListId=10&passYear=2002&passListType=Person&uniqueId=4G6N&datatype=Person |archive-date=2008-05-19 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>
