{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2017}} {{Orphan|date=October 2016}}
'''Kate Fay''' is an award-winning New Zealand chef and food writer based in [[Auckland]]. She is also part-owner of a top city restaurant.<ref name=":1" />
Fay was born and raised in Auckland. Her mother, Bev Fay, ran a milkbar and Fay spent some time working in it, which she later said taught her how to work under pressure.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/lifestyle/news/article.cfm?c_id=6&objectid=10381170|title=Sometimes, mother does know best|last=MacFarlane|first=Kirsten|date=10 May 2006|newspaper=New Zealand Herald|language=en-NZ|issn=1170-0777|access-date=25 October 2016}}</ref>
Fay began her working life as an adult in an office, before going travelling overseas. She first visited London and then Israel, where she lived on a [[kibbutz]] for eight months and cooked in its kitchen. She decided to become a chef and returned to London to work in restaurants there.<ref name=":1" /> She later returned to New Zealand and in 1999 she was appointed head chef of the [[Parnell, New Zealand|Parnell]] restaurant Cibo.<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/food/2013-09/22/content_16984261.htm|title=Reaching across asia – chinadaily.com.cn|last=穆伟|first=|date=|website=www.chinadaily.com.cn|publisher=|access-date=25 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/lifestyle/news/article.cfm?c_id=6&objectid=11248306|title=Women battle to make the cut as top chefs|date=2 May 2014|newspaper=New Zealand Herald|language=en-NZ|issn=1170-0777|access-date=25 October 2016}}</ref> In 2003 she became a part-owner of the restaurant.<ref name=":1" />
== Awards and recognition == Fay was voted Best Auckland Chef in 2004, and in the same year Cibo was voted the second Best Restaurant.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://www.wheelers.co.nz/spb/new-zealand/publisher/8766-hachette/?sort=lowestpriced&status=international&page=11|title=Books published by Hachette – Wheelers Books|website=www.wheelers.co.nz|access-date=25 October 2016}}</ref> Cibo also holds the Beef and Lamb Excellence Award and has been nominated in the [[Metro (magazine)|Metro]] Top 50 Restaurants awards and [[Cuisine (magazine)|Cuisine]] Restaurant of the Year awards. In 2010 and 2012 it was named Metro Best Smart Casual restaurant.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.eventfinda.co.nz/2013/an-evening-with-cibors-kate-fay/auckland/mt-eden|title=An Evening with Cibo’s Kate Fay|website=Eventfinda|access-date=25 October 2016}}</ref>
